cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with resource allocation in wireless powered relay networks, which involves optimizing the transmission of both information and power. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes a bargaining game approach to balance the objectives of different parties, which falls under game theory (cs.GT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes simulation results, which suggests that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
